gov.nasa.worldwind.geom
Class Sector

java.lang.Object
  gov.nasa.worldwind.geom.Sector
All Implemented Interfaces:
Cacheable, Comparable<Sector>, Iterable<LatLon>
public class Sector
extends Object
implements Cacheable, Comparable<Sector>, Iterable<LatLon>

Sector represents a rectangular reqion of latitude and longitude. The region is defined by four angles: its minimum and maximum latitude, its minimum and maximum longitude. The angles are assumed to be normalized to +/- 90 degrees latitude and +/- 180 degrees longitude. The minimums and maximums are relative to these ranges, e.g., -80 is less than 20. Behavior of the class is undefined for angles outside these ranges. Normalization is not performed on the angles by this class, nor is it verifed by the class' methods. See Angle for a description of specifying angles.

Sector instances are immutable.

See Also:
Angle

fromProjectedBounds

public static Sector fromProjectedBounds(double minX,
                                         double maxX,
                                         double minY,
                                         double maxY,
                                         AVList params)
Creates a new Sector which bounds the specified projected bounding rectangle, according to the specified projection parameters. The coordinates are assumed to be non-geographic. If the specified parameter list describes a UTM projection, this is equivalent to calling fromUTMBounds(double, double, double, double, gov.nasa.worldwind.avlist.AVList), where the X and Y coordinates correspond to the UTM easting and northing, respectively. This returns null if the parameter list describes an unrecognized projection.

Parameters:
minX - the minimum X coordinate.
maxX - the maximum X coordinate.
minY - the minimum Y coordinate.
maxY - the maximum Y coordinate.
params - parameter list describing the projection.
Returns:
a new bounding Sector bounding the specified projected rectangle.
Throws:
IllegalArgumentException - if the parameter list is null.

fromUTMBounds

public static Sector fromUTMBounds(double minEasting,
                                   double maxEasting,
                                   double minNorthing,
                                   double maxNorthing,
                                   AVList params)
Creates a new Sector which bounds the specified UTM bounding rectangle, according to the specified UTM projection parameters. The parameter list must define the UTM zone and hemisphere in the parameters WorldFile.WORLD_FILE_ZONE and WorldFile.WORLD_FILE_HEMISPHERE, respectively.

Parameters:
minEasting - the minimum UTM easting, in meters.
maxEasting - the maximum UTM easting, in meters.
minNorthing - the minimum UTM northing, in meters.
maxNorthing - the maximum UTM northing, in meters.
params - parameter list describing the UTM projection.
Returns:
a new bounding Sector bounding the specified UTM rectangle.
Throws:
IllegalArgumentException - if the parameter list is null, or if it does not contain the parameters WorldFile.WORLD_FILE_ZONE and WorldFile.WORLD_FILE_HEMISPHERE.

intersectsSegment

public boolean intersectsSegment(LatLon begin,
                                 LatLon end)
Determines whether this sector intersects the specified geographic line segment. The line segment is specified by a begin location and an end location. The locations are are assumed to be connected by a linear path in geographic space. This returns true if any location along that linear path intersects this sector, including the begin and end locations.

Parameters:
begin - the line segment begin location.
end - the line segment end location.
Returns:
true true if this sector intersects the line segment, otherwise false.
Throws:
IllegalArgumentException - if either the begin location or the end location is null.

splitBoundingSectors

public static Sector[] splitBoundingSectors(Globe globe,
                                            LatLon center,
                                            double radius)
Returns an iterable of Sectors encompassing a circle centered at a given position, with a given radius in meters. If the geometry defined by the circle and radius spans the international dateline, this will return two sectors, one for each side of the dateline. Otherwise, this will return a single bounding sector.

Parameters:
globe - a Globe instance.
center - the circle center location.
radius - the circle radius in meters.
Returns:
the circle's bounding sectors.

union

public final Sector union(Sector that)
Returns a new sector whose angles are the extremes of the this sector and another. The new sector's minimum latitude and longitude will be the minimum of the two sectors. The new sector's maximum latitude and longitude will be the maximum of the two sectors. The sectors are assumed to be normalized to +/- 90 degrees latitude and +/- 180 degrees longitude. The result of the operation is undefined if they are not.

Parameters:
that - the sector to join with this.
Returns:
A new sector formed from the extremes of the two sectors, or this if the incoming sector is null.
